Miscellaneous Highlights: The first match of the Pakistan vs Ireland T20I series will begin on May 10 at the Clontarf Cricket Club in Dublin.
The Pakistan vs Ireland T20I series will be played in Dublin at the Clontarf Cricket Club.
The Pakistan T20I squad has been announced, with Babar Azam as captain.
The Ireland T20I squad has been announced, with Paul Stirling as captain.
The series will be live streamed on Fancode app in India, but it is not free as the user have to give Rs 69 to purchase their tour pass subscription.
The Pak vs Ire T20 match will not be available on television in India.
Others: The Pakistan Cricket Team is set to face Ireland at home in a three-match T20I series following a drawn series with New Zealand.
Pakistan, lacking access to the IPL platform, is engaged in T20 series to prepare for the upcoming tournament.
